This paper deals with applying deep learning techniques to medical corpora to identify relationships from unstructured text. The paper specifically uses the word2vec deep learning toolkit to identify properties of pharmaceuticals based on mid-sized, unstructured medical text corpora available on the web. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR), which are covered by the arXiv sub-categories cs.CL and cs.IR. Additionally, the paper evaluates the efficiency of word2vec in identifying relationships, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (AI), covered by the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with medical data, which could also fall under the cs.CY sub-category for computers and society.
